'''''Star Wars Insider'' 32''' is the thirty-second issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in Winter [[1997]]. Issue 32 celebrated the theatrical release of ''[[The Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition]]'' as well as the twentieth anniversary of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' franchise. This issue unveiled a new design for the magazine, including a new ''Star Wars Insider'' logo, which lasted through [[Star Wars Insider 76|issue 76]] in Spring [[2004]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk" {{C|by Jon Bradley Snyder}}
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by Dan Madsen with [[Rick McCallum]]}}
*"[[Star News]]"
*"[[Lucasfilm's Latest]]"
*"[[In the Star Wars Universe|In the ''Star Wars'' Universe: Shelagh Fraser]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*"[[The Wonder Column|The New Wonder Column]]" {{C|by [[Anthony Daniels]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]"
*"[[The Horse's Mouth|Straight from the Horse's Mouth]]" {{C|by [[Bob Cooper]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Rebel Pilot Reunion]]" {{C|by [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]}}
*:<small>Now it can be told: The amazing stories of the actors who played Rebel pilots! Jon Bradley Snyder spent almost a year tracking down these chaps and finding out what it was really like under the helmet.</small>
*"[[Bridge to the Universe: Digital Technology and the Making of The Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition|Bridge to the Universe: Digital Technology and the Making of ''The Star Wars Trilogy'' Special Edition]]" {{C|by [[Mark Cotta Vaz]]}}
*:<small>Famed special effects scribe Mark Cotta Vaz puts the Special Edition and the short history of digital effects in crystal-clear perspective with this exclusive article.</small>
*"[[20 Years Ago Today: An Anniversary Toast to Star Wars|20 Years Ago Today: An Anniversary Toast to ''Star Wars'']]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>George Lucas, and a wide range of celebrities and ''Star Wars'' folk recount their first memories of seeing ''Star Wars'' in theater. Scott Chernoff introduces it all with a moment of reflection.</small>
*"[[Caravan of Courage: Star Wars on Television|''Caravan of Courage'': ''Star Wars'' on Television]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>The tireless Mr. Chernoff gives a sweeping overview of ''Star Wars'' on the small screen, including a look at ''Star Wars'' and muppets that just might surprise you.</small>

